The Telegraph - Calcutta : Business

 Business Briefs

 Dhaka, May 7: Local steel manufacturers in Bangladesh have said they would oppose any deal that would provide a long-term guaranteed gas supply to the Tatas, who are now planning to set up steel units in that country. They demanded that the government settle the proposed gas supply deal with the Tatas on the basis of international prices.

 New Delhi, May 7: Michelin has ruled out setting up a manufacturing unit in India until sales of truck and bus radial tyres gain further momentum after its joint venture with Apollo tyres failed to take off. In April 2004, Michelin and Apollo had formed a joint venture to manufacture a range of truck and bus radials for the Indian market. 

 Tokyo, May 7: Top Japanese brokerage houses are expanding their operations in Asia, including India, to capitalise on robust demand for funds in the fast-growing region, a report said.

 Moscow, May 7: The market capitalisation of Gazprom soared over $300 billion, making it the world?s third largest company following US oil company Exxonmobil and General Electric.

 New Delhi, May 7: The probe by the investigating arm of the Monopolies and Restrictive Trade Practices Commission (MRTPC) into the Rs 2,300-crore buyout of Air Sahara by Jet Airways has got delayed. The companies have sought more time to file replies to queries.




